=> Chat Model

    -> Purpose

        -> The Chat Model is responsible for communicating with the selected LLM.
        -> It receives the user's prompt, sends it to the selected LLM, and returns the generated response.
        -> It does not maintain memory, load documents, use tools, or perform reasoning.
        -> Its only responsibility is to interact with the selected LLM.

    -> Configuration

        -> Credential
            -> API Key used to authenticate with the LLM provider.

        -> Model Name
            -> Specifies which model should process the request.

            -> Examples
                -> gemini-2.5-flash
                -> gpt-4.1
                -> claude-3.5-sonnet

        -> Temperature
            -> Controls the randomness and creativity of the generated response.

        -> Additional Parameters

            -> Max Tokens
            -> Top-P
            -> Top-K
            -> Frequency Penalty
            -> Presence Penalty

    -> Flow

            User Prompt
                ↓
            Chat Model
                ↓
            LLM Provider API
                ↓
            Selected LLM
                ↓
            Response

    -> Important

        -> A Chat Model only communicates with the LLM.
        -> It does not manage prompts, memory, tools, or RAG.

=> Chat Prompt Template

    -> Purpose

        -> Creates the final prompt that will be sent to the LLM.
        -> Combines the System Message and Human Message into a single prompt.
        -> It does not communicate with the LLM directly.

    -> Components

        -> System Message

            -> Defines the behavior or personality of the AI.

            -> Examples

                -> You are a Java Expert.
                -> Answer only in JSON.
                -> You are a Travel Assistant.

        -> Human Message

            -> Represents the user's actual input.

            -> Examples

                -> What is Spring Boot?
                -> Explain Docker Volumes.

    -> Flow

            System Message
                    +
            Human Message
                    ↓
            Final Prompt
                    ↓
            Send to LLM Chain

    -> Important

        -> The Prompt Template only prepares the prompt.
        -> It never communicates directly with the LLM.

=> LLM Chain

    -> Purpose

        -> Acts as the orchestrator between the Prompt Template and the Chat Model.
        -> Receives the Prompt from the Chat Prompt Template.
        -> Receives the configured Chat Model.
        -> Invokes the selected LLM.
        -> Returns the generated response.

    -> Flow

            Chat Prompt Template
                    +
            Chat Model
                    ↓
                LLM Chain
                    ↓
            Invoke Selected LLM
                    ↓
            Return Response

    -> Important

        -> The LLM Chain coordinates the execution.
        -> It combines the Prompt and Chat Model to generate the final response.